    "summary": "Building a sustainable future together with creative Leadership and focus on execution excellence.\n\nCompany Athlete profile Luyten van den Berg, BA, MSc\n\nLuyten van den Berg, healthcare executive, studied at the sports academy in Amsterdam and Erasmus University in Rotterdam. He specialized in sports management and marketing management and innovation. After a top sport challenge at the Dutch Ski Association, he worked for a pharmaceutical company, AstraZeneca for 22 years. In various roles in Sales Management, Marketing Management, Regional Market Access and Commercial Excellence and multichannel management (SFE / BI / KAM / MCM / Commercial Policy) at national and international level. In recent years he has designed and managed various business transformations, showing that change management is flowing through his blood with an eye for people and organization. People centred transformation with the aim to help unlock the full potential of the organization is my drive and passion.  A conceptual energetic, creative thinker and doer, who can give strategic and operational direction to the challenges in your organization. You get an open, no-nonsense style of communication and approach with the aim of achieving growth together. A people-oriented business leader. #create high impact #leadership by example #lead with creativity.\n\nLuyten has been facilitator and speaker at different conferences and in-company events. \n\nSome of the topics : Leadership in changing environments - increasing your digital impact - ONE Strategy, ONE Team, ONE Voice to the Customer - Account Management an obsolete commercial model in Pharma? - Omnichannel all the way - Call anxiety:Decreased impact in an omnichannel world - The future of pharma in healthcare\n\nSTRATEGY | INTERIM MANAGEMENT | FACILITATION | EXECUTIVE | COACHING |TEAM BUILDING | KEY ACCOUNT MANAGEMENT | BUSINESS MODEL INNOVATION | MULTICHANNEL MANAGEMENT",
